United States flew into New York on an Air Force jet Wednesday and
presented herself as a potential candidate to replace Sen. Daniel
Patrick Moynihan upon his retirement next year. It was, by any
measure, a remarkable day in the politics of both New York and the
nation. By Adam Nagourney. With photos.
</P>
<P>
   FLA-TOBACCO-SUIT (Undated) _ A Florida jury finds against the
nation's biggest tobacco companies in the first class-action case
to reach a verdict, holding that they are guilty of conspiring to
hide the danger and addictiveness of cigarettes. The six-person
jury in a Miami state court also said that both compensatory and
punitive damages could be awarded, throwing open the door to
hundreds of thousands of potential claims by current and former
smokers in Florida. By Barry Meier.
</P>
<P>
