<P>
   SOC-WOMEN-IMAGE (Los Angeles) _ To a large extent, the players
on the American women's soccer team have been willing participants
in the sexualization of the team in recent years. Mia Hamm has been
named one of People magazine's 50 most beautiful people. Defender
Brandi Chastain has appeared in Gear magazine, crouched behind a
soccer ball, wearing only her cleats and her rippling muscles. With
their ponytailed-virtuosity, the American players have also sent a
calculated message around the world: that women can be both
athletic and feminine in a sport that, in many places, still
carries the stigma that women who play are somehow unwomanly. By
Jere Longman.
