<P>
   TRAVEL-BABIES _ Traveling with a little kid van make you imagine
scenarios that keep DFACS busy. Calling it an adventure is like
describing a marathon as a long race. You can imagine the
challenge, but you'll never truly know how exhausting it can be
until you've done it yourself. After the memory of all the hassles
subsides, a certain elation sets in from enduring it all. Johanna
has flown 19 times now, and I look at loading up all her
necessities like the provisioning of a small miltia. Keeping this
29-pound dervish entertained for an amount of time in close
quarters and the phrase ``by any means necessary'' comes to mind.
(Hiskey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) with ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
