   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-BABYTIPS _ The keys to happy travel with baby are smart
packing, strategic scheduling and a minimalist approach when it
comes to pre-planned activities. Forget vacation as you knew it --
if it's high-energy, go-get-em activities you crave, pack your
scuba gear and your water skis and leave Junoir with your in-laws.
Or wait until he's old enough to participate. Here's how we tackled
some of the challenges of traveling with a little one.
(Williamson/McCafferty, Atlanta Journal-Constitution freelancers;
not for use by NYTNS clients). with ILLUSTRATION AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-LONDONBABY _ We decided to take up a friend on an offer
to stay in his London flat, with our two girls, Hannah, 4, and
Bella, 2. We'd been tickled that Bella believed us when we told her
we were going to London to see the Queen. But as the day for our
Buckingham Palace visit approached, we regretted having raised her
expectations. The trip was gruelling enough without having to deal
with a pretty major letdown for a 2 year old. (Reiss, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution freelancers; not for use by NYTNS clients).
with ILLUSTRATION AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-JASMINEHILL _ ELMORE COUNTY, Ala. _ At Montgomery's
Jasmine Hill Gardens, sometimes referred to as ``Alabamas Little
Corner of Greece,'' it's easy to lose yourself in the past. Not
just the near past of the 1920s, which is when Benjamin and Mary
Fitzpatrick created this 20-acre hilltop Eden. Or the pre-Civil War
era of their tiny cottage, surrounded by flowers and trees. Or even
the distant days of their impressive collection of ancient Greek
sculptures. For beneath all of that, quite literally, is the
footprint of a cataclysmic event that occurred some 80 million
years ago. Toward the end of the age of the dinosaurs, the county
seat of Wetumpka was hit by a meteorite that left a crater four
miles wide. (Townsend, Atlanta Journal-Constitution freelancers;
not for use by NYTNS clients). with COLOR PHOTO AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
