<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   MOVING-FURNITURE _ As adults, we rarely take the time to allow
ourselves anything quiet and calming. Well, picture this: sinking
into the depths of an oversized chair swing or glider, sipping a
tall glass of lemonade, listening to the chirpy, buzzing sounds of
summer while a soft breeze fans your face _ all in the tranquil
privacy of your own porch or yard. The increasing demand for moving
furniture, mainly swings and gliders, is a reawakening that is
partly nostalgia, partly decorative and mostly, just plain
relaxing. (Dayton Daily News). 25. HEAT-COMFORT _ A couple weeks
ago we talked about the efficient use of air conditioner, fans and
shade trees to keep your home comfortably cool at reasonable cost
this summer. Today we'll go over a few other tips associated with
summer comfort and energy efficiency. James Cummings' Nuts and
Bolts column, (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 27.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   BUFFETT-PARROTHEADS _ The Parrothead phenomenon. Unlike the
Grateful Dead fans known as Deadheads, Parrotheads neither bathe in
patchouli nor twitch and twirl as if at a Summer of Love ``be-in.''
They've got too many frequent flier miles to be part of the
counterculture. And though they might take a few days off to catch
some Jimmy Buffett concerts, they've usually got to be at work in
the morning. Such distinctions are important to the faithful
Parrothead, for whom fellowship and community service are as
important as the wacky garb. It's something that impressed the
``Today'' staff when Buffett made a recent appearance on the show,
cheered on by a gazillion sign-waving Parrotheads. (Dollar, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
