<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL 0713 _ Traveling with a little kid is quite a
challenge, but you'll never truly know how exhausting it can be
until you've done it yourself. (Hiskey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes 3-column color illustration of
woman holding suitcases and a child.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   INFO BOX _ A list of places to take the family for fun and
excitement. (Staff, Cox News Service) Art includes 2-column color
photo of go-karts on a track.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL BRIEFS _ Chicago has installed portable heart
defibrillators at Midway and O'Hare Airports. The battery-powered
devices, Hewlett-Packard Heartstream Forerunners, are no more than
a minute apart at walking speed. (Staff, N.Y. Times News Service)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-BABIES _ Traveling with a little kid van make you imagine
scenarios that keep DFACS busy. Calling it an adventure is like
describing a marathon as a long race. You can imagine the
challenge, but you'll never truly know how exhausting it can be
until you've done it yourself. After the memory of all the hassles
subsides, a certain elation sets in from enduring it all. Johanna
has flown 19 times now, and I look at loading up all her
necessities like the provisioning of a small miltia. Keeping this
29-pound dervish entertained for an amount of time in close
quarters and the phrase ``by any means necessary'' comes to mind.
(Hiskey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) with ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-BABYTIPS _ The keys to happy travel with baby are smart
packing, strategic scheduling and a minimalist approach when it
comes to pre-planned activities. Forget vacation as you knew it --
if it's high-energy, go-get-em activities you crave, pack your
scuba gear and your water skis and leave Junoir with your in-laws.
Or wait until he's old enough to participate. Here's how we tackled
some of the challenges of traveling with a little one.
(Williamson/McCafferty, Atlanta Journal-Constitution freelancers;
not for use by NYTNS clients). with ILLUSTRATION AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-LONDONBABY _ We decided to take up a friend on an offer
to stay in his London flat, with our two girls, Hannah, 4, and
Bella, 2. We'd been tickled that Bella believed us when we told her
we were going to London to see the Queen. But as the day for our
Buckingham Palace visit approached, we regretted having raised her
expectations. The trip was gruelling enough without having to deal
with a pretty major letdown for a 2 year old. (Reiss, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution freelancers; not for use by NYTNS clients).
with ILLUSTRATION AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-JASMINEHILL _ ELMORE COUNTY, Ala. _ At Montgomery's
Jasmine Hill Gardens, sometimes referred to as ``Alabamas Little
Corner of Greece,'' it's easy to lose yourself in the past. Not
just the near past of the 1920s, which is when Benjamin and Mary
Fitzpatrick created this 20-acre hilltop Eden. Or the pre-Civil War
era of their tiny cottage, surrounded by flowers and trees. Or even
the distant days of their impressive collection of ancient Greek
sculptures. For beneath all of that, quite literally, is the
footprint of a cataclysmic event that occurred some 80 million
years ago. Toward the end of the age of the dinosaurs, the county
seat of Wetumpka was hit by a meteorite that left a crater four
miles wide. (Townsend, Atlanta Journal-Constitution freelancers;
not for use by NYTNS clients). with COLOR PHOTO AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-SOUTHEAST _ We list Family Fun reader's picks of 14 best
Southeastern vacation destinations for families. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 11.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY _ ``Unto These Hills'' in Cherokee, N.C., is one of the
oldest of the outdoor historical dramas that dot the landscape of
the South. We talk with some of the Atlanta actors who are in the
show that focuses on the removal of the Cherokees from their native
land. Also, a listing of 15 other historical dramas from Alabama,
Kentucky, Tennesee, Virginia. (Hamilton, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-FESTIVALS _ Southern happenings. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
