<P>
   &UR; MISSILE Washington Perlez  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; exclusive  &LR; The Administration is expressing concerns about the
recent visit of the Saudi defense minister to Pakistani nuclear
facilities and lack of explanation by the Saudis. Officials fear
Saudis might be interested in replacing their old Chinese missiles,
and that Pakistan is becoming more of a weapons supplier.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PENTAGON Washington Myers  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Tentative Ralston, vice chairman of the joint chiefs, talks
today about the Pentagon review of the air war that's under way.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PROLIF  &LR;   &UR; Washington Schmitt  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; exclusive  &LR; The Government's efforts to combat the spread of
chemical, biological and nuclear weapons is an uncoordinated mess,
says a new independent commission created by Congress, which
implicitly criticizes Clinton for a lack of leadership and
recommends a new White House czar to oversee the issue.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNET Washington Sanger  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department releases an extensive study on access to
the Internet, looking at gaps in access to technology and
information.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ELECT Washington Clymer  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   It's not just George Bush, but everybody who is raising a ton of
campaign money. There's more of it around than anyone can remember.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CLINTON Calif. Purdum  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton winds up his poverty tour with a visit to a
youth training academy in LA.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WEST Washington Becker  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Togo West, secretary of veterans affairs, plans to resign, amid
growing criticism by veterans' groups of budget cutbacks and
investigations into his traveling expenses.
</P>
