<HEADLINE>
(ATTN. S.C.)  
 PLAYBOY MODEL: `IT'S NOT VOGUE, BUT ...' 
</HEADLINE>
  (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients. Non-subscribers
can make individual purchase by calling (888) 603-1036 or (888)
346-9867.) 
(mk) 
 By JOSE FRANCO   
 Herald-Journal, Spartanburg, S.C.   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREENVILLE, S.C. _ In high school, Brooke Richards was voted the
girl most likely to appear on the cover of Vogue magazine.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not Vogue exactly, but it's close,'' Richards said about
her July cover of Playboy magazine.
</P>
<P>
   The 22-year-old model from nearby Walhalla is clad in a gold
bikini on the July issue and is featured in a section called ``The
Girls of Hawaiian Tropic.'' The 10-page spread was shot in Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's exciting, it's an accomplishment to me,'' Richards said
at a recent magazine signing under a tent outside the Liquid
Highway, a drive-through coffee shop in Greenville. ``Some people
may not see it that way, but it is to me.''
</P>
<P>
   This is not the first time Richards has appeared nude for
Playboy. She was on the cover of Playboy's May 1998 ``Sexy Girls
Next Door'' issue and in Playboy's Girlfriends and Playboy's Book
of Lingerie in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Now, the girl next door is spending July at Playboy founder Hugh
Hefner's mansion in Los Angeles working on her centerfold, which
comes out later this year or early next year.
</P>
<P>
   ``We go to a lot of parties, we hang out around the pool,'' she
said. ``A lot of limousines drive up. And we get to meet a lot of
celebrities. But being a centerfold is a lot of long days. It's
also strenuous work.''
</P>
<P>
   Response from men for her past pictorials in Playboy helped land
her on the July cover, she said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't sit around and think that all these men want me,'' she
said. ``It never really crosses my mind. Playboy is a collector's
item. Plus I know what I look like in the mirror when I get up. I
don't deceive myself and think I'm a big star.''
</P>
<P>
   But don't tell that to the men who came out to meet her on a
recent Friday afternoon. Many were a little tongue-tied to say
hello to a Playboy cover model in the flesh. And most kept asking,
``Are you really from Walhalla?''
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't grow up there, I just moved there,'' she had to keep
repeating.
</P>
<P>
   The crowd included firefighters, police officers, telephone
workers, landscapers and women getting copies signed for
boyfriends, fathers and bosses.
</P>
<P>
   Richards, who has a flirtatious sense of humor, wrote playful
messages to many of her fans.
</P>
<P>
   Some of the autographs included notes that read, ``Last night
was memorable,'' or to some firefighters, ``Thanks for the hot
time.''
</P>
<P>
   ``She's not like the normal person you meet in Walhalla,'' said
20-year-old Joey Crowe, who had his magazine signed. ``I never
would have believed she lived in my town.''
</P>
<P>
   The magazine features her in a yellow bikini, in a blue thong
and completely naked.
</P>
<P>
   ``She is pretty easy to look at,'' said autograph-seeker Bubba
Britton, 25, of Greenville. ``She is handling all the attention
well.''
</P>
<P>
   The 5-foot-8-inch blonde beauty said she would love to parlay
that attention into an acting career.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to move to Los Angeles or San Diego but I am waiting
for just the right time,'' she said. ``I missed an audition for the
lead role in `Baywatch' and I missed an audition for `Sheena
Goddess of the Jungle.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Richards, who said she has a steady male companion, wasn't
uncomfortable undressing in front of the camera.
</P>
<P>
   The former tomboy said she had skinny-dipped a couple of times
as a teen-ager.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was a little nervous at first but Playboy makes you feel
comfortable,'' she said. ``There are five to 10 people on the set
including a makeup artist.''
</P>
<P>
   Richards, the youngest of 14 children, said some of her siblings
weren't crazy about the idea of their baby sister posing nude in a
national men's magazine.
</P>
<P>
   ``Some of my sisters are really against it because they are very
religious,'' she said. ``I think being religious is great, but
being naked is just not something I think is wrong. I grew up as a
Southern Baptist. I'm not saying what I am doing is right, but I am
comfortable with it.''
</P>
<P>
   Richards had dreamed of becoming a model since she was 4 years
old.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was always told that I was never going to make it,'' she
said. ``But negativity makes you want to achieve it even more.''
</P>
</TEXT>
