</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Deja vu is the feeling you're likely to get from
``Twice Upon a Yesterday,'' at least if you've seen any of the
other films in this minigenre. In ``Twice,'' a boozing slacker
actor named Victor (Douglas Henshall) gets a second chance after
screwing up with his girlfriend. This happens not because of the
generosity of her heart, but because he meets a couple of quixotic
characters who allow him to turn back time and _ well, if he had to
do it all over again, he'd do it differently, right? Isn't that
always the way? By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
