<P>
   MICHELIN _ Anderson County and Stephens County, Ga., are the
finalists for a $400 million Michelin tire plant that could employ
up to 350 people, the Anderson Independent-Mail reported. Officials
in both counties say Michelin is leaning heavily toward Anderson
County because of the work force and because South Carolina
recently passed a law giving tax breaks to tire-manufacturing
companies, the newspaper reported Thursday. The French-based tire
giant is not expected to make a final decision until September.
Several cities and counties were in the running originally, but the
competition has narrowed to the two counties apart 45 miles apart,
said Rep. Cordell Maddox Jr., D-Anderson, who has worked with
Michelin and Anderson County officials. (Kempner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NDC-MEDSCAPE _ Atlanta-based National Data Corp., a health
information company, is joining CBS Corp. in buying a stake in
Medscape Inc., an online provider of medical information for health
care professionals. NDC is investing $10 million, plus an
additional $10 million in other considerations. CBS, which is
buying a 35 percent stake in Medscape, will work with the company
to create a new health care site aimed at consumers. Currently the
site is geared toward medical professionals, providing articles
from medical journals, news on conferences and other information
for doctors, nurses and other members of the health care
profession. In exchange, CBS gets $150 million worth of promotion
over the next seven years. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-POLLUTION _ The state's environmental commission last week
approved new rules to reduce sulfur in gasoline as a way of
reducing pollution, but it won't take effect until 2004 to give
refiners time to alter equipment. Austin and San Antonio had asked
the commission to speed up compliance, to as soon as 2001, as a way
of cleaning up their air -- and helping to avoid tipping into
non-compliance with federal clean air rules. (Hight, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: ATTENTION TEXAS EDITORS.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
