<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-ATLANTARECORDS _ Fulton County Superior Court Judge
Bensonetta Tipton Lane holds hearing over the disputed eight boxes
of records from the 1996 Olympics. The Georgia Amateur Athletic
Foundation filed a lawsuit against state Attorney General Thurbert
Baker and The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, which have been pushing
for the release of the boxes arguing that the Olympic records are
subject to the Georgia Open Records Act. GAAF owns the records.
(Croft, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
