   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   HILLARY-TOUR _ Hillary Clinton takes her New York ``listening
tour'' to Cooperstown and Utica. (Vejnoska, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   NEWT _ Consulting work for Freddie Mac and commentaries on the
same radio network that airs Rush Limbaugh are just the latest
undertakings by the very busy former speaker of the House. Newt
Gingrich sits on several boards, is affiliated with a
California-based think tank and delivers speeches for what
reportedly are hefty fees. (Sherman, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   BLACK-COLLEGES _ WASHINGTON _ Sallie Mae and the College
Fund/UNCF hold a news conference to release study results and
recommendations for historically black colleges and universities
with high student loan default rates. (Dart, Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   DIGITAL-DIVIDE _ WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department releases a
report, ``Falling Through the Net: Defining the Digital Divide,''
updating its assessment of the technology and information gap in
America. (Geewax, Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-POLITICS _ WASHINGTON _ The Republican National
Committee announces an ``e.GOP Project'' that it says will give its
candidates an unprecedented ability to communicate, organize,
register voters and raise money via the Internet. (Glass, Cox News
Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
