Kansas City is starting to show some results. About 10,000 new
streetlights gleam in the city. Nearly 7,000 more are being
installed. And about 11,000 more are in various planning stages.
The project, approved by voters in November 1997, promises to make
Kansas City one of the country's best-lit cities. By MATT STEARNS.
Story will move in the ``a'' category.
