<HEADLINE>
TOP SEED CONTINUES MARCH IN MEN'S 45 EVENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICH HAMMOND  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WESTLAKE VILLAGE, Calif. _ After the first two mathes Thursday,
it was starting to look bad for the eight seeded players in the
USTA men's 45-and-over hardcourt tennis championships.
</P>
<P>
   Fifth-seeded Phillip Kadesch and eighth-seeded Larry Belinsky
were eliminated in two of the morning matches at the Westlake
Tennis and Swim Club, but fortunately for the favored, the upsets
stopped there. The remaining six seeds all won their round-of-16
matches to advance to today's quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
   The top seed, Gene Malin of Woodland Hills, continued his run
through the tournament with a 6-2, 6-3 victory over Kurt Nielsen of
Porterville.
</P>
<P>
   Malin advances to face Pete Kelly of Palm Springs, one of
Thursday's two upset winners, who knocked off Belinsky 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
   The other unseeded winner, Tom Lightvoet of Costa Mesa, earned a
6-3, 6-4 victory over Kadesch of North Easton, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   Third-seeded Wesley Jackson of Albuquerque, N.M., had little
trouble in a 6-2, 6-0 victory over Chris Robb.
</P>
<P>
   The remaining four seeds each faced a challenge in the afternoon
matches, but each survived with three-set victories.
</P>
<P>
   Second-seeded Wendell Pierce of Oakland, who had dropped only
two games in his round-of-32 victory on Wednesday, fell behind but
rallied against Skip Walther of Columbia, Mo., to win 3-6, 6-2,
6-3.
</P>
<P>
   A little rest wasn't enough help for Andrew Stanley of
Camarillo. On Wednesday, Stanley's opponent and friend, Jurgen
Janson, retired rather than play a third set against Stanley,
saying he wanted to allow his friend to rest for his round-of-16
match against Peter Bronson.
</P>
<P>
   The sixth-seeded Bronson, of Scottsdale, Ariz., defeated Stanley
6-2, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
   In the longest match of the day, fourth-seeded Gewan Maharaj of
Tampa, Fla., had the endurance to outlast Tom Jaklitsch of Islip,
N.Y., 7-6 (10-8), 4-6, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
   Seventh-seeded Bob Wright of Temecula got an early scare but
rallied to beat Rich Causey of Atlanta, 3-6, 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
   In today's quarterfinals at 11 a.m., Malin will face Kelly and
Jackson will take on Lightvoet. In the 12:30 p.m. matches, Bronson
takes on Maharaj and Wright faces Pierce.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
