   (NYT1) BOSTON -- July 8, 1999 -- BBO-ALLSTAR-IMPACT-BOS, 07-08
-- The Hynes Veterans Memorial Convention Center on Wednesday.
Major League Baseball's All-Star Game opens with the John Hancock
FanFest at the Hynes on Friday. Companies are striving to promote
the game and the events surrounding it, hoping to polish their
images by association. Tourism officials see a promotional bonanza
with an impact long after the last baseball fan leaves. And
observers say the huge event will help the Red Sox demonstrate why
they need a new stadium. (Frank/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
