<SLUG> BC-BALZER-PUBLISHER-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BOB BALZER NAMED PUBLISHER AT DAILY BULLETIN IN INLAND EMPIRE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY DAILY NEWS  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ONTARIO _ Veteran Southern California newspaper executive Bob
Balzer was named publisher of the Inland Valley Daily Bulletin in
Ontario on Thursday by Ike Massey, president and CEO of the Los
Angeles Newspaper Group and publisher of the Daily News.
</P>
<P>
   The 49-year-old Balzer, who has been vice president of
advertising and marketing for LANG since 1996, will assume the new
post Aug. 1. The Bulletin has a circulation of 69,534 daily and
73,873 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Bob has a proven track record of success in the newspaper
industry. He will be good for Bulletin readers, advertisers and
employees,'' Massey said.
</P>
<P>
   Before joining LANG, Balzer had been advertising director at the
San Bernardino County Sun for three years. Earlier he was group
advertising manager at the Los Angeles Times, where he worked for
17 years. He joined the Ontario Daily Report in 1970.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is truly completing a circle in my career,'' Balzer said.
``To publish this newspaper in the Inland Empire, where I've lived
most of my life, is a dream come true.''
</P>
<P>
   Balzer replaces Mike Ferguson, who will rejoin Donrey Media
Group, the previous operators of the Bulletin. LANG, which is based
at the Daily News in Woodland Hills, took over management of the
Bulletin and the Sun earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the Daily News, the Bulletin and the Sun, the Los
Angeles Newspaper Group operates the Long Beach Press-Telegram, the
Pasadena Star-News, the San Gabriel Valley Tribune, the Whittier
Daily News, the Redlands Daily Facts, the Hemet News and the Lompoc
Record.
</P>
<P>
   LANG's combined daily circulation is 601,265, and Sunday
circulation is 641,827.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
