<SLUG> BC-HOTEL-ACQUISITION-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CORPORATION ACQUIRES MANAGEMENT CONTRACTS ON SEVERAL HOTELS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MARK P. COUCH  
 c. 1999 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Buckhead America Corp. of Atlanta announced
Thursday that it had acquired management contracts on 12
limited-service hotels in Missouri and Kansas.
</P>
<P>
   Under the agreement, Buckhead will take over management of eight
Super 8 hotels and four Country Hearth Inns that had been run by
Quality Lodging LLC, a Kansas City hotel developer.
</P>
<P>
   The purchase price of the management contracts wasn't disclosed,
but Buckhead said it would pay a combination of cash and Buckhead
stock valued at a minimum $7 a share.
</P>
<P>
   Buckhead's stock closed down 1/4 at 5 5/8 Thursday on the Nasdaq
Stock Market.
</P>
<P>
   Patrick Wallace, spokesman for Buckhead, said the company was
taking over contracts on hotels that were part of a previous
agreement between Buckhead and Quality Lodging.
</P>
<P>
   Under that contract, Quality Lodging had agreed to develop 12
Country Hearth Inns during a five-year period, with options for an
additional 22 properties.
</P>
<P>
   Two of the Country Hearth Inns have opened and are included in
the transaction announced Thursday. Buckhead said it would manage
additional Country Hearth Inns developed by Quality Lodging.
</P>
<P>
   Executives with Quality Lodging were not available for comment
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   In a prepared statement, Gary Sirna and Stephen Danner,
principals with Quality Lodging, said they would be able to
accelerate the development of new Country Hearth Inns by
transferring management responsibilities to Buckhead.
</P>
<P>
   Wallace said the Missouri hotels in the transaction were in
Chesterfield, Chillicothe, Columbia, three in Kansas City, Mount
Vernon, North Kansas City, Platte City, Riverside and Smithville.
Wallace said the Kansas hotel was in Gardner.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
